page_title: Azure OpenAI Service Assistants Python & REST API reference
page_description: Learn how to use Azure OpenAI's Python & REST API with Assistants.
chunk_content: Retrieve assistant file```httpGET https://YOUR_RESOURCE_NAME.openai.azure.com/openai/assistants/{assistant_id}/files/{file-id}?api-version=2024-05-01-preview```Retrieves an Assistant file.Path parameters|Parameter| Type | Required | Description ||---|---|---|| assistant_id | string | Required | The ID of the assistant the file belongs to. ||file_id| string | Required | The ID of the file we're getting |### ReturnsThe assistant file object matching the specified ID### Example retrieve assistant file# Python 1.x```pythonclient = AzureOpenAI(    api_key=os.getenv("AZURE_OPENAI_API_KEY"),      api_version="2024-05-01-preview",    azure_endpoint = os.getenv("AZURE_OPENAI_ENDPOINT")    )assistant_file = client.beta.assistants.files.retrieve(  assistant_id="asst_abc123",  file_id="assistant-abc123")print(assistant_file)```# REST```consolecurl https://YOUR_RESOURCE_NAME.openai.azure.com/openai/assistants/{assistant-id}/files/{file-id}?api-version=2024-05-01-preview  \  -H "api-key: $AZURE_OPENAI_API_KEY" \  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' ```---
